Martin Vargic used satellite data to chart how the constellation stars have shifted and will change in the future . 
  He estimated how the constellations will change from 50,000 BC to 100,000CE . 
  The Big Dipper will become a duck and Orion will lose his head . 
  The chart shows how the position of the stars has changed over time . 
  Some of the most distinctive constellation will become unrecognisable in 98,000 years . 
 